lling explanation for the shifting, unstable, and violent nature of the political and military system of the southern dynasties. Offering a wider perspective which considers the social world beyond the capital elite, the book challenges earlier conceptions of medieval society as "aristocratic" and rooted in family lineage and officeholding.Andrew Chittick is E. Leslie Peter Associate Professor of East Asian Humanities at Eckerd College.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aCommunity lifezChinazXiangyang FuxHistoryyTo 1500. 0aGarrisonszChinazXiangyang FuxHistoryyTo 1500. 0aPatronage, PoliticalzChinazXiangyang FuxHistoryyTo 1500. 0aSocial systemsxHistoryyTo 1500. 4aAsian Studies : Asian Studies. 4aAsian Studies : Chinese Studies. 4aHistory : History. 7aHISTORY / Asia / China.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143842899440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438428994423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438428994/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles